cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper involves the development of a deep learning model for plant disease identification using hyperspectral data, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of saliency maps for explaining the model's predictions suggests a focus on interpretability and explainable AI, which could also place the paper in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of hyperspectral data and the identification of the most sensitive wavelength could also relate to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
